Others: The Raptors started their first lineup with RJ Barrett, Scottie Barnes, Immanuel Quickley, Jakob Poeltl, and Gradey Dick.
The game marked the first time all season that this lineup had played together.
The Raptors lost the game to the Milwaukee Bucks with a score of 128-104.
RJ Barrett scored 25 points and had 9 rebounds, Scottie Barnes scored 21 points and had 5 assists, and Immanuel Quickley scored 11 points and had 3 assists in their first game together.
